      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that tariffs are necessary to protect domestic jobs is a valid one, and it's often framed as a choice between sacrificing jobs in the short-term to protect them in the long-term. The reality is that many domestic industries have become complacent and inefficient, relying on cheap imports to prop up their businesses. By imposing tariffs, the US can level the playing field and force these industries to innovate and compete on their own terms, ultimately creating more sustainable and better-paying jobs.",
      "source": "target",
